 much for his country. \u003ca href=\"https://www.army.mil/article/121005/soldier_champ_joe_louis_sacrificed_much_for_his_country\"\u003eArmy.mil\u003c/a\u003e.\u003cbr /\u003eJoe Louis (Barrow), “The Brown Bomber.” \u003ca href=\"https://www.arlingtoncemetery.mil/Explore/Notable-Graves/Sports/Joe-Louis\"\u003eArlington National Cemetery\u003c/a\u003e.","dropCap":false},"innerBlocks":[]},{"clientId":"a5be19c2-4ab1-4c7d-9478-0615b163f188","name":"corpnews-blocks/banner","attributes":{"heading":"HISTORY Vault: Black History","text":"\u003cp\u003eWatch acclaimed Black History documentaries on HISTORY Vault.\u003c/p\u003e","bgMediaID":42105,"bgMediaURL":"https://assets.editorial.aetnd.com/uploads/2023/03/blackHistoryMonth_16x9-1.jpg","ctaEnabled":true,"ctaURL":"https://watch.historyvault.com/topics/black-history","ctaButtonText":"WATCH NOW","ctaNewTab":false},"innerBlocks":[]}]},"excerpt":{"rendered":"Joe Louis Early Life Joe Louis was born Joseph Louis Barrow on May 13, 1914 in Lafayette, Alabama. He was the seventh of eight children and a grandson of slaves. His parents made a modest living: His father, Mun Barrow, was a sharecropper, while his mother, Lillie Barrow, was a laundress. When he was 2 […]","protected":false},"featured_media":9216,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"video_platform_id":"","video_duration":0,"video_content_rating":"","video_disable_autoplay":false,"subhead":"","exclude_from_rss":false,"distribute_scheduled_post":[],"curated_related_posts":"","disable_related_posts":""},"tags":[],"article_type":[],"story_byline":[406],"attribute":[7],"story_category":[67],"article_type_meta":"","tags_meta":"","disable_interrupter":"","primary_term":null,"video_thumbnail":false,"hide_on_google_news":false,"yoast_head_json":{"title":"Joe Louis - Boxing, Record \u0026 Max Schmeling | HISTORY","description":"Joe Louis was the world's heavyweight boxing champion for nearly 12 consecutive years, a period that saw his famed knockout of Germany's Max Schmeling in 1